   149	## <a id="_Toc207966451"></a>__3\.01 Request Management__
   150	
   151	3\.01\.01 Your Business Requirements
   152	
   153	1. Support 20\+ distinct request types including design requests, labor quote requests, customer approvals, proposal requests, and demo requests
   154	2. Enable request engine configuration with conditional logic and automated routing based on request type, customer segment, and team assignments
   155	3. Provide custom request type creation and management capabilities for specialized workflows \(GSA, storage agreements\)
   156	4. Support request routing for both internal team assignments and external vendor coordination
   157	5. Enable request template and field management with dynamic form behavior based on user responses
   158	6. Implement request approval workflows and automated notifications for status changes and escalations
   159	7. Maintain request status tracking and lifecycle management with complete audit trails
   160	
   161	3\.01\.02 Current State Process
   162	
   163	Pivot currently manages all pre\-quote requests through Adobe Workfront's "Issues" system, which serves as their comprehensive request management platform\. The system supports extensive request types including general requests, design double checks, labor quote requests \(both simple and complex\), customer approval workflows, bill backs, and various proposal types \(standard, GSA\-specific, leasing, third\-party billing, storage agreements\)\.
   164	
   165	Salespeople initiate project requests through Workfront questionnaire systems that automatically assign project types based on answers, creating sophisticated workflows with conditional logic\. Request routing occurs through automated logic where IPMs receive complex projects while sales reps handle transactional work directly\. The system includes specialized workflows for demo requests requiring delivery coordination and quote bypass processes for specific order types \(WIX, ServiceNet, Delivery Upon Receipt \(DUR\), Quick Quotes, warranty claims\)\. This will be included in the requirement list\.
   166	
   167	Key pain points include manual data transfer between Workfront, IQ Coordinator, and D365 for financial processing, heavy dependence on individual expertise \(particularly Sherri Nuzum's Workfront knowledge\), and the complexity of managing 20\+ request types that may include redundant variations creating training challenges for new team members\.
   168	
   169	3\.01\.03 Orion/NetSuite Solution
   170	
   171	Orion/NetSuite provides comprehensive request management capabilities specifically designed to eliminate the manual coordination and system fragmentation that currently challenges Pivot's operations\. The envisioned solution includes a configurable request engine that supports unlimited request types with sophisticated conditional logic, automated routing rules, and integrated approval workflows that have been successfully implemented across hundreds of commercial furniture dealerships\.
   172	
   173	The platform's request engine configuration enables complex business rules through standard administration tools, supporting everything from simple general requests to sophisticated multi\-stage approval processes\. Request template and field management capabilities provide dynamic form behavior where fields appear based on previous responses, replicating Pivot's current Workfront questionnaire logic\. The solution's request routing functionality automatically assigns requests based on configurable criteria including customer segment, project complexity, and team member specialization\.
   174	
   175	Request approval workflows and notification systems provide automated status tracking and escalation management, while request lifecycle management maintains complete audit trails for compliance and process improvement\. The integrated approach eliminates manual data transfer between systems by providing native integration between request management and downstream financial, project, and resource planning functions\.
   176	
   177	3\.01\.04 Future State Process
   178	
   179	After implementation, Pivot's request management will operate through Orion/NetSuite's unified request engine where salesp\. Oeople or other approved roles initiate requests through configurable forms that automatically capture all necessary information and route to appropriate team members based on business rules\. The system will support many of the current request types through streamlined categories with dropdown selections and replacement of current request types by tasks, eliminating the complexity of managing 20\+ separate forms while maintaining functionality\.
   180	
   181	Additionally, those requests that were used to hand the baton from one department to the next will be handled naturally in the Orion/NetSuite system since all users will be working within one platform\. Things like transactions or record statuses will serve as natural handoffs to departments\.  Orion allows the initial assignment and reassignment of the labor quote request as needed\.
   182	
   183	Request routing will allow for assigning of  PMs to complex projects based on salesperson alignment while directing transactional requests to sales coordinators\. Demo requests allows the  collection, delivery, and contact information while triggering fulfillment workflows, and specialized requests\.  Orion provides labor quote functionality for internal and external \(union\) labor\.
   184	
   185	The integrated platform will provide real\-time visibility into request status, approval workflows, and process metrics while maintaining the sophisticated business logic Pivot has developed, but without the complexity of managing multiple systems and manual handoffs\.
