105:Pivot Interiors requires a unified platform to replace their current fragmented system landscape consisting of Adobe Workfront, D365, Power BI, and FluidPay for managing pre\-quote activities\. The company processes complex design and labor quote requests across multiple market segments \(Enterprise, Venture, Public Health Care, Government\) with sophisticated workflows that currently require extensive manual coordination between systems\.
149:## <a id="_Toc207966451"></a>__3\.01 Request Management__
151:3\.01\.01 Your Business Requirements
155:3. Provide custom request type creation and management capabilities for specialized workflows \(GSA, storage agreements\)
161:3\.01\.02 Current State Process
163:Pivot currently manages all pre\-quote requests through Adobe Workfront's "Issues" system, which serves as their comprehensive request management platform\. The system supports extensive request types including general requests, design double checks, labor quote requests \(both simple and complex\), customer approval workflows, bill backs, and various proposal types \(standard, GSA\-specific, leasing, third\-party billing, storage agreements\)\.
165:Salespeople initiate project requests through Workfront questionnaire systems that automatically assign project types based on answers, creating sophisticated workflows with conditional logic\. Request routing occurs through automated logic where IPMs receive complex projects while sales reps handle transactional work directly\. The system includes specialized workflows for demo requests requiring delivery coordination and quote bypass processes for specific order types \(WIX, ServiceNet, Delivery Upon Receipt \(DUR\), Quick Quotes, warranty claims\)\. This will be included in the requirement list\.
167:Key pain points include manual data transfer between Workfront, IQ Coordinator, and D365 for financial processing, heavy dependence on individual expertise \(particularly Sherri Nuzum's Workfront knowledge\), and the complexity of managing 20\+ request types that may include redundant variations creating training challenges for new team members\.
173:The platform's request engine configuration enables complex business rules through standard administration tools, supporting everything from simple general requests to sophisticated multi\-stage approval processes\. Request template and field management capabilities provide dynamic form behavior where fields appear based on previous responses, replicating Pivot's current Workfront questionnaire logic\. The solution's request routing functionality automatically assigns requests based on configurable criteria including customer segment, project complexity, and team member specialization\.
177:3\.01\.04 Future State Process
183:Request routing will allow for assigning of  PMs to complex projects based on salesperson alignment while directing transactional requests to sales coordinators\. Demo requests allows the  collection, delivery, and contact information while triggering fulfillment workflows, and specialized requests\.  Orion provides labor quote functionality for internal and external \(union\) labor\.
189:*​​*Pivot currently uses 57 distinct issue types to create various types of requests in the following 10 categories: Design Related, Finance, General, Labor Quote, Order Entry, Other, Pre\-Sale, Proposal \(Quote\), Punch, and Service\.
191:The 57 distinct issue types are now mapped to 24 types in Orion\. 33 of the current distinct types map to an existing standard Orion process\.
