469:3\.02\.01 Your Business Requirements
477:3\.02\.02 Current State Process
481:The current process lacks standardization for requirements collection and often relies on informal communication between team members\. Job site analysis information may be captured in Workfront projects, email communications, or estimator notes, creating inconsistency in data quality and availability for quote accuracy\.
489:3\.02\.04 Future State Process
507:3\.03\.01 Your Business Requirements
515:3\.03\.02 Current State Process
517:Pivot's project initiation currently occurs through Workfront with salespeople creating project requests through questionnaire systems\. Projects are automatically categorized based on responses, with IPMs assigned for complex projects while transactional work routes directly to sales coordinators\. The system provides project\-level visibility across all related orders and maintains umbrella project structure for comprehensive customer management\.
519:Project setup involves manual coordination between Workfront project creation and D365 financial setup, requiring sales coordinators to transfer project information for quote creation and customer financial dimension configuration\.
527:3\.03\.04 Future State Process
549:3\.04\.01 Your Business Requirements
557:3\.04\.02 Current State Process
559:Pivot tracks design capacity through Workfront time tracking with an 80% utilization target, supported by Power BI reporting that blends data from multiple systems\. Users \(Design Studio Leads\) manage all design assignments based on both capacity availability and project\-specific skill requirements, with assignment decisions occurring at the request level\.
561:Design double\-check processes involve detailed markup logs that track error types and quality metrics, providing valuable reporting data but requiring manual form completion and coordination\. The current system requires manual coordination between Workfront time entries and Power BI reporting for complete visibility into designer utilization and project profitability\.
571:3\.04\.04 Future State Process
573:Design workflow management will operate through integrated Orion Kanban Boards where users can view real\-time designer capacity, current project assignments, and design request queues in visual workflow displays\. Assignment decisions will be supported by automatic capacity calculations and project expertise matching while maintaining human oversight for optimal quality outcomes\.
587:## <a id="_Toc207966455"></a>__3\.05 Team & Assignment Management__
589:3\.05\.01 Your Business Requirements
591:1. Implement Order Team Management \(People Assignment Utility\) for automated team assignments across projects
592:2. Enable team management by Sales Person maintaining current PM \(including IPM\) \-salesperson alignment relationships
598:3\.05\.02 Current State Process
600:Pivot uses a sophisticated hybrid team assignment approach where Implementation Project Managers \(IPMs\) are aligned to specific salespeople and handle their complex projects, while users manage all design resource assignments regardless of salesperson alignment\. This creates a matrix organization that optimizes both customer relationship continuity and resource utilization\.
602:Project creation triggers IPM assignment based on salesperson alignment and project complexity, with sales coordinators handling simple transactional projects without IPM involvement\. The current system provides project\-level team visibility across the entire lifecycle from request through completion but requires manual coordination to maintain team assignments and resource balancing\.
606:Orion/NetSuite provides comprehensive team and assignment management through the Order Team Management \(People Assignment Utility\) that supports sophisticated resource allocation models used by professional services organizations\. The solution enables automated team assignments while maintaining flexibility for manual adjustments and exception handling that Pivot requires\.
608:Team management by Sales Person functionality preserves current IPM\-salesperson relationships while providing capacity\-aware assignment recommendations for optimal resource utilization\. Role\-based assignments and responsibilities ensure appropriate skill matching and workload distribution, while influencer and customer contact assignment capabilities support complex project communication coordination\.
612:3\.05\.04 Future State Process
614:Team assignments will occur automatically through Order Team Management rules that maintain IPM\-salesperson relationships while enabling user optimization of design resources\. The system will provide cross\-functional visibility into team assignments and project status through integrated dashboards that eliminate manual coordination requirements\.
630:3\.06\.01 Your Business Requirements
638:3\.06\.02 Current State Process
640:Pivot's customer approval process currently defaults new customers to 100% prepayment terms, with D&B credit checks performed by the accounting team and credit applications processed early in the sales cycle\. FluidPay handles credit card processing with fee pass\-through capabilities, but the system is described as "basic but functional" with limited integration to D365\.
652:3\.06\.04 Future State Process
