# Codex Review — §3.03 Pre-Quote

## Headline assessment
Not lock-ready. Structure and tone are mostly sound, but D-1/D-2/D-4 need source reconciliation before Matt/Pivot leadership see it.

## Standards compliance
Clean on banned terms: no `spec'd`, `2.5×`, R/Y/G, or obvious bad § references.

Issue: source citations are too loose for the standard. Divergences cite broad `Pre-Quote.md §3.01` instead of requirement-level / line-specific anchors, despite the citation rule in [drafting-standards.md:155](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/working/drafting-standards.md:155>).

Issue: line 78 says “KBM’s BRD,” but the section itself says no KBM BRD exists. Use “KBM source material” instead. See [05 - Pre-Quote.md:6](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:6>) and [05 - Pre-Quote.md:78](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:78>).

## Source accuracy
Pivot 57 -> 24 across 10 categories is accurate. Source: [Pivot Pre-Quote.md:189](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:189>) and [Pivot Pre-Quote.md:191](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:191>).

Material issue: KBM labor types are not reconciled with the later gap analysis. Draft treats Internal, External, Intermarket, LTS as carried-forward types; v2 says active types are Third Party and Intermarket, with Internal/LTS inactive. Compare [05 - Pre-Quote.md:61](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:61>) to [GapAnalysis v2:81](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/Pre-Quote/KBMH/3%20Output/GapAnalysis_PreQuote_Labor_Quotes_v2.0_COMPREHENSIVE.md:81>) and [GapAnalysis v2:354](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/Pre-Quote/KBMH/3%20Output/GapAnalysis_PreQuote_Labor_Quotes_v2.0_COMPREHENSIVE.md:354>).

Material issue: job site analysis is not KBM-only. Pivot has explicit Requirements Management / job site analysis requirements. Move it to “Explicit in both.” See [05 - Pre-Quote.md:36](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:36>) vs. [Pivot Pre-Quote.md:471](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/working/pivot-brds-md/Pre-Quote.md:471>).

Material issue: Joe is missing. KBM source names Joe as technical dependency for vendor fields and labor quote acceptance validation. See [Requirements Map:88](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/Pre-Quote/KBMH/3%20Output/Requirements_Map_PreQuote_v1.0.md:88>) and [GapAnalysis v2:247](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/Pre-Quote/KBMH/3%20Output/GapAnalysis_PreQuote_Labor_Quotes_v2.0_COMPREHENSIVE.md:247>).

## Tone calibration
Mostly calibrated. “Exceeds Pivot’s framing” is a little comparative; soften to “KBM’s source provides more detailed vendor-management requirements.” See [05 - Pre-Quote.md:18](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:18>).

## Cross-area consistency
RFP ownership is too broad. Marketing owns RFP coordination, but CRM explicitly defers task/resource assignment and project/folder timing to Pre-Quote. Compare [05 - Pre-Quote.md:182](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:182>) with [01 - CRM (Sample).md:176](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/01%20-%20CRM%20(Sample).md:176>) and [cross-area-decisions.md:119](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/working/cross-area-decisions.md:119>).

Missing division-taxonomy dependency. D-8 relies on divisional routing, but CRM D-3b is still a working-session decision. See [05 - Pre-Quote.md:166](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:166>) and [cross-area-decisions.md:21](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/working/cross-area-decisions.md:21>).

Approval, document storage, pipeline, GP, and multi-company/contact cross-references are generally sound.

## Template fidelity
§3.03.1 through §3.03.8 structure is sound.

Decision table math reconciles: 9 rows, footer says 9 decisions. See [05 - Pre-Quote.md:207](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:207>) and [05 - Pre-Quote.md:219](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:219>).

But D-1 request-type math does not reconcile operationally: 24 Pivot types plus KBM labor types could imply more than 24 unless KBM categories are explicitly subtypes/values inside Labor Quote. See [05 - Pre-Quote.md:65](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:65>).

## Decision quality
D-1: sound direction, needs count/subtype reconciliation.

D-2: not complete. Add PO-as-acceptance, multi-line acceptance, multiple accepted quotes by scope, auto-rejection logic, and 15% labor GP cross-reference. Sources: [GapAnalysis v2:157](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/Pre-Quote/KBMH/3%20Output/GapAnalysis_PreQuote_Labor_Quotes_v2.0_COMPREHENSIVE.md:157>), [GapAnalysis v2:184](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/Pre-Quote/KBMH/3%20Output/GapAnalysis_PreQuote_Labor_Quotes_v2.0_COMPREHENSIVE.md:184>), [GapAnalysis v2:220](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/Pre-Quote/KBMH/3%20Output/GapAnalysis_PreQuote_Labor_Quotes_v2.0_COMPREHENSIVE.md:220>), [GapAnalysis v2:245](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/Pre-Quote/KBMH/3%20Output/GapAnalysis_PreQuote_Labor_Quotes_v2.0_COMPREHENSIVE.md:245>).

D-3: sound, but name the Joe/technical validation dependency or intentionally anonymize it.

D-4: not lock-ready. Launch point is only half the issue; scope source-of-truth is pending Matt/Kimi decision. See [05 - Pre-Quote.md:112](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:112>) and [GapAnalysis v2:190](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/Pre-Quote/KBMH/3%20Output/GapAnalysis_PreQuote_Labor_Quotes_v2.0_COMPREHENSIVE.md:190>).

D-5/D-7/D-8: sound.

D-6: okay as a capability, but distinguish send-back-for-info from auto-rejection of competing labor quotes.

## Reconciliation principle audit
By decision row: KBM-lean 4 (D-2, D-3, D-4, D-6); Pivot-lean 3 (D-1a, D-7, D-8); hybrid 2 (D-1b, D-5). Balanced enough after source fixes.

## What's missing
KBM: scope governance, multiple accepted labor quotes, auto-rejection logic, PO acceptance, 15% labor GP deduction, external pre-quote URL linkage, Google Drive/SharePoint file strategy.

Pivot: Project Navigator / Master Project / Related Projects from Project Initiation; site-condition address-level questions; design capacity / Design Studio Lead assignment details.

## Internal commentary
Remove or move “Pivot stakeholder review” from open questions; it reads like project-process tracking, not a BRD input. See [05 - Pre-Quote.md:249](</Users/marcusdallacqua/Documents/KBMH-Pivot-Implementation/_Unification/05 - Pre-Quote.md:249>).

## Recommended edits before lock
1. Rework D-1 to preserve the 24-type math and classify KBM labor categories as Labor Quote subtypes unless leadership truly wants new request types.
2. Rewrite D-2/D-4 around the v2 labor-quote gap analysis: active types, PO acceptance, scope-based re-quote, auto-rejection, multiple acceptance validation, scope source of truth.
3. Move job site analysis to explicit-in-both.
4. Add cross-area row for RFP mechanics owned by Pre-Quote/Operations, distinct from Marketing D-8.
5. Add division taxonomy dependency and tighten all divergence source citations.
